-- Fed adds reserves via 3-day repurchase agreement
-- 
-- Fri Aug 17, 2007 9:33am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/08/17/us-markets-fedops-idUSNYG00070420070817

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - The U.S. Federal Reserve said on Friday it added temporary reserves to the banking system through 3-day repurchase agreements. 

 Federal funds, the benchmark overnight lending rate to banks, last traded at 5.19 percent, below the Fed's targeted rate of 5.25 percent.